CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 5, 1955, pg. 25A reads: "Champion - The amazing Louise Fulton, Pittsburgh's champion female bowler, outscored Carole Collins of Chicago during a recent bowling exhibition in the Windy City. Miss Fulton is easily one of the best bowlers among women in the game.  She is currently coaching a mixed group of bowlers of the NAACP. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Louise Fulton wearing tweed skirt, eyeglasses, and light colored short sleeved sweater, holding marbled bowling ball, posed in front of sign reading "H. Williams 212, V. Fitzgerald 237, L. Payne 203, M. Hannon 223, V. Thomas 205, L. Fulton 245"
